              A <strong>custom woodworker</strong> transforms plain drywall rooms into architecturally rich spaces
              with built-in bookshelves, coffered ceiling details, hand-profiled crown molding, and statement fireplace surrounds.
            </p>
            <p>
              At <a href="/" class="text-yellow-600 font-bold hover:underline">First Class WoodWorks</a>,
              we use the same traditional joinery and professional finishing techniques on a fireplace mantel
              that we use on a $30,000 kitchen — dovetail joints, mortise-and-tenon construction, and
              post-catalyzed conversion varnish on every piece. There's no "B-team" material or shortcut finishing
              on our smaller projects.
            </p>
          </section>

          <div class="bg-zinc-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-600 p-8 my-10 reveal">
            <h4 class="text-zinc-900 font-bold mb-2">Master Woodworker Pro-Tip:</h4>
            <p class="italic">"The most impactful upgrade in a living room isn't the TV — it's the built-in wall unit that frames it. A floor-to-ceiling entertainment center with integrated lighting and adjustable shelving transforms a flat wall into the architectural focal point of your home. It's the first thing guests notice and the last thing you'd ever want to remove."</p>
          </div>

          <section class="reveal">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-4">Custom Woodworking Services</h2>
            <p>
              Every project is designed, built, and installed by our own team — no subcontractors, no flat-pack assembly.
